content_vision: The singer sitting alone in a dimly lit room, writing in a journal or playing a guitar. Close-up shots of tears streaming down the singer's face as she sings about her pain. Flashbacks of happy moments with a former partner, contrasted with present-day scenes of the singer dealing with heartbreak. The singer standing in front of a microphone, pouring her heart out while surrounded by candlelight.
structure_suggestion_description: The singer standing in front of a microphone, pouring her heart out while surrounded by candlelight
text:
Intro:
As I sit alone in this dimly lit room, my heart heavy with hurt and regrets,
I can feel your memories surge, like unrelenting tides that I can't forget.

Chorus:
But as I look into the mirror, I see a broken reflection of what I used to be,
torn apart by love, a shattered heart that only you can see.
But all I see is a stranger, a face I thought I knew,
now it's just a painful reminder of the love we once knew.

Verse 1:
I can feel my mask of happiness slipping away,
revealing a heart that's broken and trying to stay.
But as I look into the mirror, I see a broken reflection of what I used to be,

But as I try to numb the pain with this pen and paper,
the memories just grow stronger instead.
But as I try to numb the pain with this pen and paper,
the memories just grow stronger instead.

Pre-Chorus 1:
But as I try to numb the pain with this pen and paper,
the memories just grow stronger instead.

Verse 2:
But as I look into the mirror, the mask of my broken heart starts to fade,
and I see the strength and resilience that I have gained.
But as I look into the mirror, the mask of my broken heart starts to fade,
and I see the strength and resilience that I have gained.
But as I look into the mirror, I see my strength shining through,
a survivor who has grown from the love I once knew.
Through the pain and the tears, I found strength I never knew existed,
and in this brokenness, I've become a masterpiece in the midst of it.

Pre-Chorus 2:
But with every tear that falls, I find strength in letting go,
and in these broken pieces, I'll build a new version of my soul.

Bridge:
But as I rise from these ashes, I find my true worth,
and I'll never let anyone dim my light on this earth.
But as I rise from these ashes, I find my true worth,
and I'll never let anyone dim my light on this earth.
No more playing small, I'll shine brighter than the sun,
my heart may have been shattered, but now I know I've won.

Outro:
But as I walk away from you, with tears in my eyes,
I know it's time for me to heal and rise.

Instrumental:
Lost in the melody, my heart aches for what used to be,

has a bridge and final chorus for a climactic finish
ends with an outro to bring the song to a close.

ends with a final chorus to conclude the song

ends with a final chorus and outro to close the song

ends with a bridge and final chorus for a dynamic finish

includes an instrumental break and bridge for variation

ends with a final chorus and outro to close the song

ends with an outro to bring the song to a close.
